> Another work day, another dinner daydream. You're sitting at your desk and 2:00 p.m. rolls around. Suddenly, all you can think is, "Dinner...what the heck am I going to eat for dinner?!" Well, we've got you covered, and FYI, the answer to that question is pretty delicious. We're serving up Southwest-spiced chicken with tangy green salsa and melty Monterey Jack, plus hearty rice and black beans—all baked in our handy, oven-ready aluminum trays to make cleanup a breeze. To finish things off, the chicken is drizzled with a sweet and smoky red pepper crema. Talk about a dream come true!

== Chicken ==

Adjust rack to middle position and preheat oven to 425 degrees.

Pat @chicken cutlets{10%ounce} dry with #paper towels{} and season all over with half the @Southwest spice blend{1%tablespoon} (you'll use the rest in the next step), @salt{} and @pepper{}. Place in 1 #oven-ready aluminum tray{} (divide between 2 trays for 4 servings). Cover with @green salsa{7.06%ounce}.

Bake on middle rack until chicken is cooked through, ~{22-28%minutes}.

== Rice 'n' Beans ==

While chicken bakes, massage @microwaveable jasmine rice{1} in package to break up grains. Transfer to a #medium bowl{}.

Drain @black beans{13.4%ounce}, reserving liquid. To bowl with rice, add drained beans, @chili powder{1%teaspoon}, remaining Southwest spice, 1 TBSP reserved bean liquid (2 TBSP for 4 servings), ¾ tsp salt (1 1/2 tsp for 4), and pepper; stir to combine.

Transfer to remaining oven-ready aluminum tray (divide between remaining 2 trays for 4). Top with 3 TBSP @butter{3%tablespoon} (use 3 TBSP butter per tray for 4) and cover tightly with #foil{}.

Bake on middle rack until rice and beans are warmed through and butter has melted, ~{15-18%minutes}.

== Broil and Serve ==

Once chicken is cooked through, remove from oven and heat broiler to high. Spoon green salsa from tray over tops of chicken (it's okay if there's still some salsa around the chicken). Top chicken with @Monterey Jack cheese{¼%cup}.

Broil until cheese is melted and lightly browned, ~{2-3%minutes}.

> Watch carefully to avoid burning.

Let cool slightly.

Fluff rice 'n' beans with a #fork{} to combine with melted butter; season with salt and pepper. Divide between plates and top with chicken and green salsa. Drizzle with @smoky red pepper crema{4%tablespoon} and serve.